## Method 3: Build from Source

If you prefer to build the provider from source:

### Prerequisites

- Rust toolchain (1.70.0 or later)
- Git

### Build Steps

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_ORG/hemmer-provider-{{ provider_name }}.git
cd hemmer-provider-{{ provider_name }}

# Build in release mode
cargo build --release

# The binary will be at:
# - macOS: target/release/libhemmer_{{ provider_name }}_provider.dylib
# - Linux: target/release/libhemmer_{{ provider_name }}_provider.so
# - Windows: target/release/hemmer_{{ provider_name }}_provider.dll
```

### Install

Copy the built binary to your Hemmer providers directory:

**macOS:**
```bash
mkdir -p ~/.hemmer/providers
cp target/release/libhemmer_{{ provider_name }}_provider.dylib \
   ~/.hemmer/providers/hemmer-provider-{{ provider_name }}
chmod +x ~/.hemmer/providers/hemmer-provider-{{ provider_name }}
```

**Linux:**
```bash
mkdir -p ~/.hemmer/providers
cp target/release/libhemmer_{{ provider_name }}_provider.so \
   ~/.hemmer/providers/hemmer-provider-{{ provider_name }}
chmod +x ~/.hemmer/providers/hemmer-provider-{{ provider_name }}
```

**Windows:**
```powershell
New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path $env:USERPROFILE\.hemmer\providers
Copy-Item target\release\hemmer_{{ provider_name }}_provider.dll `
          $env:USERPROFILE\.hemmer\providers\hemmer-provider-{{ provider_name }}.exe
```

